message.content:
cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a system to enforce privacy protection in social networks and discusses methods to preserve the privacy of social network users.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper focuses on social networks and proposes a new scheme that can be applied to most existing ones.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses a transparent data storage and accessing mechanism according to users' credentials.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper addresses privacy concerns in social networks and proposes a solution that empowers users to define their own privacy requirements.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the behavior of the proposed system in two well-known social networks and emphasizes the importance of providing transparent access to sensitive contents.
